Package: opennars-native
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: atomspace
Description: Non-Axiomatic Reasoning System in pure C
 OpenNARS for Applications (ONA) is a lightweight implementation of
 the Non-Axiomatic Reasoning System (NARS) in pure C. It provides
 real-time reasoning capabilities with minimal dependencies.
 .
 Features:
  - Non-Axiomatic Logic (NAL) implementation
  - Event-driven architecture
  - Real-time inference
  - Narsese language parser
  - Network NAR support for distributed reasoning
 .
 This package integrates with AGI-OS cognitive architecture for
 unified reasoning capabilities.

Package: opennars-native-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libdevel
Depends: opennars-native (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: OpenNARS for Applications - development files
 This package contains the header files and static libraries needed
 to build applications that use the OpenNARS API.
